The course offers an introduction to the history of the University of Tartu in the context of the broader intellectual history of universities in Europe. We will study the development of the European universities from the perspective of intellectual history, and get acquainted with the history of academic disciplines and traditions of teaching in Europe and Estonia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goals of the course: -	to introduce the history of the University of Tartu in the context of the broader intellectual history of universities in Europe, -	to give a basic understanding of the development of the European universities from the perspective of intellectual history, -	to introduce the history of academic disciplines and traditions of teaching in Europe and in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student: - has acquired basic knowledge of the history of the University of Tartu, - has acquired basic knowledge of the societal role and historical development of European universities, - has acquired basic knowledge of the history of academic learning and research in Europe and Estonia.
